Citation.sAbstract: Consistent isobaric vapour liquid equilibrium data have been measured for 2-butanone + ethanol,  2-butanone + 1-propanol, and 2-butanone + 2-propanol at 20 and 101.3 kPa. The binary systems 2-  butanone + ethanol and 2-butanone + 2-propanol present a minimum boiling azeotrope at both pressures,  and showthat the azeotropic compositions is strongly dependent on pressure. The equilibrium datawere  correlated using the Wilson, NRTL, and UNIQUAC models for which the parameters are reported.
Citation.sTitle: Isobaric vapour liquid equilibria for binary systems of 2-butanone with ethanol, 1-propanol, and 2-propanol at 20 and 101.3 kPa
